Our favorite, local, mom and pop’s mama-san and papa-san’s) sushi restaurant. Pre-pandemic, our kids loved picking sushi from the little sushi boats and all the staff were so nice. Now, during the pandemic, it’s pretty much just mama-san and papa-san trying to keep their restaurant alive after 15 years!
Great sushi and fun for the whole family. It’s my kids favorite place to eat out.
big yummys
Consistently good and fresh food, excellent service, great neighborhood place, family friendly. Mamasan knows her regular customers. Can't wait for them to open again.
Great food!!!

A wonderful hidden gem with delicious sushi and very friendly service. The owners clearly take great pride in producing delicious food served with a smile. Their lunch bento boxes are also at a very reasonable price with a wide variety of options.
The food is delicious and priced reasonably. The owner and wait staff are always nice.

This is my favorite sushi places in the East Bay, and i grew up here- amazing sushi, amazing and lovely staff, great atmosphere for birthdays, big parties, dates- the Vegas roll is bomb, the 2.00 happy hour Sake is amazing!
The service is regularly speedy, excellent vibes, very kind staff. I will visit here again when I arrive nearby.
Always been a good sushi place. When I moved to Oakland 10 years ago from the city (I was spoiled food wise), we found this place and we became a fan. Carry some cash to tip the sushi chef.

Whenever I'm in town, I always make it a point to take my nephew here because its his favorite spot for sushi and Mama San ALWAYS takes such good care of us. She has watched my nephew grow up and even sent  some soup and the grilled hamachi …
Great sushi spot an reasonable prices i will be coming back

I would like to begin this review by saying I have been a long time patron of Samurai Sushi Boat on Grand Lake Oakland. I began going here to eat in 2013 and have had nothing but positive opinions regarding the quality of food and service …
Great service!

Sushi is good and not too expensive here. We enjoy the sushi boat experience, it makes it a game and the kids love it. Aside from that they have some large tables for groups. Good location on Grand avenue with parking outside.
Surely a place worth visiting, the food is good and well prepared, the prices are reasonable and it is regularly well organized in here. Fantastic work.

We have been going to "the sushi boat" since opening day almost 15 years ago. We love the friendly owner, consistent food, and reasonable prices. Even though it's no longer our neighborhood place, we go back once in a while, and always for birthdays- they're great!

This is one of the few places with the conveyer boats of sushi that remind me of Japanese style sushi bars.  They make an array of delicious offerings, including the stuffed mushroom and jalapeño tempura, alongside some good staples like your standard California rolls and Tuna sashimi. Prices are very reasonable, and they have mochi.
